                                PortageLive
                         Runtime translation server

This directory contains the files you need to install a trained PortageII
system on a translation server.  We call this PortageLive.

To fully setup a PortageLive server, you need
 - software (see bin/)
 - web service (see www/)
 - a properly configured machine (see va/)
 - models (built from framework, not from here)

Please read the "PortageLive Manual" section of the PortageII User Manual for
detailed instructions.

Subdirectories:
   bin/         tools to build the PortageLive runtime software layout
   models/      tools to build the PortageLive models layout
   www/         web service software, and tools to install it
   scripts/     scripts shared between all of the above
   va/          documentation for OS and OS-provided software required to run
                PortageLive, including how to create a PortageLive Virtual
                Appliance (VA).
   python/      tools to create a custom python package for PortageLive VMs
